    "body": "The issue is still present.  Maybe if I use pictures the issue will become clearer.  Here is what the screen looks like right after clicking the Advanced button (see the repro steps above):\r\n\r\n![untitled1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7891737/50551729-698d1180-0c3a-11e9-814a-d4e321f34660.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nNotice that I have selected an ERC20 token from the dropdown, the \"Automatically calculate gas limit\" is pre-selected for me, **and the gas limit is 2100**.  That would be correct if it was an ETH transfer, but it is too low for an ERC20 transfer.\r\n\r\nI found a work-around, which probably will also highlight what the problems is.  If I **uncheck**, and then **re-check** the \"Automatically calculation gas limit\", the gas limit changes to **52094**, which is correct:\r\n\r\n![untitled2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7891737/50551693-cd630a80-0c39-11e9-8fa1-78fe487f499e.png)\r\n\r\n",
